# Half-sibling layout alignment

When fixing or testing `.ft-partner-unit-single` (child known to only one parent):

- **Do not rely on the 3-Gen Test Tree alone** to prove `alignSingleParentBranches`. That tree has half-ranks elsewhere, so `insertHalfRankSpacers` can mask the single-parent offset bug.
- Use the isolated **Half-Sibling Alignment Tree** (seed tree **5**, members 90–94, **no half-ranks**) — `LayoutOrientationTests.HalfSibling_HalfChildAlignsWithFullSiblings` fails without the JS fix.
- When applying measured rank-axis offsets in JS, **add** to `getComputedStyle(...).marginTop/marginLeft`; replacing the margin drops the CSS drop-line gap (~24px residual in horizontal).
- Couples may be inferred from shared children with no `Couple` row — match production when recreating scenarios.
